<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,1699,1883]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,349,1699,1723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Discussion.</emphasis>
This Neotropical species was previously known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1158,1700,1724]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
series from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[192,294,1732,1755]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Yucatan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[305,395,1731,1755]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Our 
<specimenCount box="[462,607,1731,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from Guadeloupe have wing lengths of 0.80 and 
<quantity box="[1201,1309,1731,1755]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.299999999999999" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="0.83">0.83 mm</quantity>
, which are considerably smaller than the 
<quantity box="[570,738,1763,1787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2349999999999999" metricValueMax="1.32" metricValueMin="1.15" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="1.2349999999999999" valueMax="1.32" valueMin="1.15">1.15-1.32 mm</quantity>
recorded for females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1149,1764,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Monohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maya">
<emphasis box="[1042,1067,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1083,1149,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">maya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Felippe-Bauer, M. L. &amp; H. Huerta &amp; S. Ibanez-Bernal" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="815 - 818" refId="ref12018" refString="Felippe-Bauer, M. L., H. Huerta, and S. Ibanez-Bernal. 2000. A new species of predaceous midge of the genus Monohelea Kieffer from Mexico (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz 95: 815 - 818." type="journal article" year="2000">Felippe-Bauer et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. However, other morphological features of the Guadeloupe females appear identical with females from 
<collectingCountry box="[256,345,1827,1851]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, so we are fairly confident of our identification of the Guadeloupe females as this species. We provide the first records of this species in the Caribbean region from Guadeloupe.
</paragraph>
